        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-25 17:35:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nUse of the hard-coded string 'process_csp' is a defect.  Unfortunately changing it in the epsdk-app-common area will cause other breakage.  The least disruptive fix to support this release this week is to extend the ONAP Portal with an alias so it recognizes requests to the endpoint 'process_csp'.  Then other applications should simply start working, without changing their POM files, without recompiling or redeploying.\n\nMay I respectfully suggest that you abandon this change?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
